org.sbml.squeezer.math
Class SBMLinterpreter

java.lang.Object
  org.sbml.squeezer.math.SBMLinterpreter
All Implemented Interfaces:
eva2.tools.des.DESystem, java.io.Serializable, org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNodeCompiler
public class SBMLinterpreter
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNodeCompiler, eva2.tools.des.DESystem

This DifferentialEquationSystem takes a model in SBML format and maps it to a data structure that is understood by the RKSolver of JavaEvA. Therefore, this class implements all necessary functions expected by SBML.

Field Detail

currentReaction

protected org.sbml.jsbml.Reaction currentReaction
This field is necessary to also consider local parameters of the current reaction because it is not possible to access these parameters from the model. Hence we have to memorize an additional reference to the Reaction and thus to the list of these parameters.

listOfContraintsViolations

protected java.util.List<java.lang.Double>[] listOfContraintsViolations
An array, which stores for each constraint the list of times, in which the constraint was violated during the simulation.

listOfEvents_delay

protected java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.Double>[] listOfEvents_delay
This array data structure stores at the position i a list of time (double values) at which the event with ID equals i must be executed. The value before last of the list ist the watcher. It can be POSITIVE_INFINITY if the trigger expession has the value trueor NaN if value of trigger expression is false

model

protected org.sbml.jsbml.Model model
The model to be simulated.

speciesIdIndex

protected java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> speciesIdIndex
This map data structure is necessary to save the index of every species within the model system since libSBML doesn't provide the index of a species for a given name. This, however, is necessary to work with an array containing the concentrations of the species.

swap

protected double[] swap
This array is to avoid to allocate memory repeatedly. It stores the values computed during the linear combination of velocities. These values are passed to the array Y afterwards.

v

protected double[] v
An array of the velocities of each reaction within the model system. Holding this globally saves many new memory allocations during simulation time.

Y

protected double[] Y
An array of the current concentration of each species within the model system.

Constructor Detail

SBMLinterpreter

public SBMLinterpreter(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model)

This constructs a new DifferentialEquationSystem for the given SBML model. Note that only a maximum of Integer.MAX_VALUE species can be simulated. If the model contains more species, this class is not applicable.

Note that currently, units are not considered.

evaluateToDouble

protected double evaluateToDouble(org.sbml.jsbml.ASTNode astnode)
Executes the mathematics of any ASTNode and returns the result.

Parameters:
astnode - A tree data structure representing the mathematics stored in an SBML file.
Returns:
a real number that is the result of the mathematics described by this ASTNode. This function return 1.0 if the evaluation of a logical expression is TRUE and 0.0 otherwise.

init

protected void init()

This method initializes the differential equation system for simulation. In more detail: the initial amounts or concentration will be assigned to every species or initialAssignments if any are executed.

To save computation time the results of this method should be stored in an array. Hence this method must only be called once. However, if the SBML model to be simulated contains initial assignments, this can lead to wrong simulation results because initial assignments may depend on current parameter values.

linearCombinationOfVelocities

protected double[] linearCombinationOfVelocities(double[] velocities)
This method computes the multiplication of the stoichiometric matrix of the given model system with the reaction velocities vector passed to this method. Note, the stoichiometric matrix is only constructed implicitely by running over all reactions and considering all participating reactants and products with their according stoichiometry or stoichiometric math.

Parameters:
velocities - An array of reaction velocities at the current time.
Returns:
An array containing the rates of change for each species in the model system of this class.
